From the original listing of the guitar:"One of the Phase 1 locking tuners was damaged and replaced with a single Phase II later in its life. The Brazilian Rosewood fretboard is in great shape and the frets have a good amount of life left, although they do show some minor divoting and moderate flattening. The original sweet switch was damaged and removed at some point as well but has been replaced with an Authentic NOS PRS replacement Sweet Switch. The original volume pot and 5 way Rotary switch are still in tact. The original tremolo back plate and control cavity cover are not pictured but are included as well." The last 3 photos are of the guitar before respray. Lollar Lollatrons are awesome pickups. The have been changed from 2 wire into 4 wire split pickups by the master wizard Dave Ulbrick.
